race.comment: STOICISM (9) failed on the quick backup with the 59kg when a plugging third over 1910m at this track. Will appreciate the weight drop from the good gate. Leading contender. MAD ANA (6) tongue-tie goes on for the first time and she ticks a few boxes today. Three weeks between runs when launched late for a solid sixth over 1800m at the Gold Coast. Nice weight drop, hard hold out. LA GRACIA (12) has been around the mark at all four runs this time in and kept fresh for this. Likely to go back from the gate and should be doing her best work late over this trip. SILVER AGENT (3) outclassed in town with a dismal seventh over 1845m at Eagle Farm. Finds an easier assignment and must be kept safe.
